Database rules:

- PostgreSQL is mandatory
- Prisma is the only DB access layer

Schema design:
- Normalize data
- Avoid duplication
- Use explicit relations
- Use indexes where appropriate

Persistence rules:
- Store only meaningful data
- Never store raw external API payloads blindly
- Always store timestamps

Migrations:
- Schema changes must be intentional
- No destructive migrations unless instructed
